Deep Seabed Mining Law Corpus — Licensing
=========================================

TWO DIFFERENT THINGS. Read both.

1) OUR CONTRIBUTIONS  ->  Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The compilation, the derived layer (structure extraction, neutral concept tags,
concept index), the schemas, the scripts, the design documents, this repository's
own text, and the generated site are licensed under CC BY 4.0.

   Human-readable deed: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
   Full legal code:     https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

You are free to share and adapt these contributions for any purpose, even
commercially, provided you give appropriate credit. Suggested attribution:

   "Deep Seabed Mining Law Corpus" (github.com/dacheah/deep-seabed-mining-law-corpus),
   used under CC BY 4.0.

2) THE SOURCE TEXTS  ->  NOT relicensed; each keeps its own terms
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The authoritative layer (authoritative/**/original.* and text.txt) reproduces
official legal texts that are NOT covered by the licence above. Each document
carries its own rights position in its metadata.yaml (license / rights_note):

  - UN treaty texts (UNCLOS Part XI, 1994 Agreement): UN materials, used with
    attribution to the United Nations.
  - ISA instruments and the draft Mining Code: official ISA documents, attributed
    to the International Seabed Authority.
  - ITLOS 2011 Advisory Opinion: official ITLOS materials, attributed to ITLOS.
  - US materials (DSHMRA; 15 CFR 970/971): U.S. Government works, public domain in
    the United States.

Nothing here is legal advice. The authoritative text of each instrument is the
official original in its authentic language; translations, structure and concept
tags are unofficial and derived. Always confirm against the cited official source.
